The paper deals with labeling schemes for forests, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). It also discusses dynamic labeling schemes, which is a subfield of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions multi-functional labeling schemes, which is related to combinatorics (cs.DM). The efficient adjacency labeling schemes for planar, bounded treewidth, bounded arboricity and interval graphs suggest that the paper may also belong to computational geometry (cs.CG) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses connectivity queries, which is a topic in social networks (cs.SI).
